description:
&lt;p&gt;Facilities Transport Services are looking to recruit drivers to help deliver a friendly, prompt and professional service on behalf of Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust. Principal duties will involve the transportation of staff and goods around Trust sites and outlying areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must hold a clean driving license and to possess a relevant qualification or experience in one or more of the following:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Violence &amp; Aggression training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conflict resolution training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vocational driver licence to class C (LGV) and D (PSV) and a current Driver CPC qualification card.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Substantial previous driving experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Security Industry Authority training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of the Security Industry especially in a large complex organisation (preferably within the NHS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of Health &amp; Safety, Moving &amp; Handling, COSHH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have good communication skills, a good geographical knowledge of Leeds and surrounding areas and must be able to work effectively in a service focused environment. There is also a significant manual handling element attached to this post associated with delivery and collection of bulk items.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware the post will require the applicant to work on rotational shift patterns which will include weekends and bank holidays in a dynamic and fast moving environment so a flexible working attitude is essential to the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are subject to a Disclosure and Barring Service records check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think you have the necessary skills to operate in a dynamic and service focused environment then we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For general enquiries in relation to these posts please contact Facilities Transport Services 0113 2063817&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For any further information please contact Simon Gallagher, Logistics Coordinator, Transport Services email:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;simon.gallgher@nhs.net&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please do not send a C.V in your email&lt;/p&gt;
